Array is a variable-like structure that can hold more than 1 value.

#file Start.js

1. Create an array
let fruits = ['apple','banana','coconut'];
console.log(fruits)

2. Index
let fruits = ['apple','banana','coconut'];
console.log(fruits[0]);
console.log(fruits[1]);
console.log(fruits[2]);

fruits[0] = 'avocado';
console.log(fruits[0]);
console.log(fruits[1]);
console.log(fruits[2]);


3. Array methods
push: add the last index
pop: delete the last index
unshift: add to the beginning
shift: delete an element from the beginning

4. length: find the number of members in an array
arrayname.length

5. indexOf: find the index of an element
arrayname.indexOf(element)

6. iterate an array: using for loop to get each element of an array

7. enhanced for loop: shortcut to displaying the element of an array
let fruits = ['apple','banana','coconut'];

#file Start.js
for(let fruit of fruits){
    console.log(fruit);
}


8. sort: method to sort 
arrayname.sort();

9. reverse sort: method to sort elements in reverse order
arrayname.reverse();

#file Start.js
let fruits = ['apple','banana','coconut'];

fruits.reverse();

for(let fruit of fruits){
    console.log(fruit);
}






